Author::::Addicks123
DateTime::::2016-03-09T21:32:03Z
Because three day matches, particularly if the weather intervened did not allow players to do things like build innings or bowl long spells. It also resulted in too many matches with contrived declarations which meant that runs and wickets were gifted in order to allow one team to set a target. The consequence being that it wasn't producing enough Test cricketers and certainly wasn't preparing them for five day matches. Another by-product was the increase in injuries and the lack of time outside of matches to practice and hone skills. 



